\f0\fs24 \cf0 STAR FRONTIER \'97 CONFIG ID STANDARD\
\
1. GENERAL RULES\
- All IDs use English only\
- All IDs use lowercase only\
- Words are separated with underscores "_"\
- No spaces\
- No hyphens\
- No Cyrillic\
- No special characters\
- IDs must be human-readable\
- IDs should be stable and not changed without real need\
\
2. ID FORMAT\
<type>_<name>\
\
Examples:\
ship_scout\
ship_frigate\
ship_trader\
weapon_pulse_laser\
weapon_light_missile_launcher\
module_shield_booster\
item_med_supplies\
planet_astra_prime\
system_helios_gate\
sector_frontier_alpha\
mission_delivery_001\
enemy_raider_light\
encounter_raider_patrol_001\
reward_raider_patrol_basic\
\
3. TYPE PREFIXES\
ship_\
weapon_\
module_\
item_\
planet_\
system_\
sector_\
mission_\
enemy_\
encounter_\
reward_\
market_\
profile_\
\
4. SCRIPTABLEOBJECT ASSET FILE NAMES\
Use readable PascalCase or split readable names for asset file names.\
\
Examples:\
Ship_Scout.asset\
Ship_Frigate.asset\
Ship_Trader.asset\
Weapon_PulseLaser.asset\
Weapon_LightMissileLauncher.asset\
Module_ShieldBooster.asset\
Item_MedSupplies.asset\
Planet_AstraPrime.asset\
System_HeliosGate.asset\
Sector_FrontierAlpha.asset\
Mission_Delivery_001.asset\
\
Important:\
- Asset file name can be readable\
- Internal Id field must follow the ID standard exactly\
\
5. GRAPHICS FILE NAMING\
\
Icons:\
icon_item_food_rations.png\
icon_item_med_supplies.png\
icon_ship_scout.png\
icon_weapon_pulse_laser.png\
icon_module_shield_booster.png\
\
